  "content": "<p>5\ufe0f\u20e3 Here&#39;s the 5th post highlighting key new features of the upcoming v258 release of systemd. <a href=\"https://mastodon.social/tags/systemd258\" class=\"mention hashtag\" rel=\"tag\">#<span>systemd258</span></a></p><p>On modern Linux systems the persistent hostname is configured in /etc/hostname. Linux people treating their devices like pets tend to come up with nice, imaginative names for their hosts.</p><p>But this doesn&#39;t scale: if you have a large number of devices to manage (i.e. &quot;cattle&quot;) then you typically want something more automatic: the hostnames used should follow some specific pattern, \u2026</p>",
